tables.table_schema: CREATE TABLE musicians (musician_id INT PRIMARY KEY, musician_name VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL, instrument VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL);
CREATE TABLE instruments (instrument_id INT PRIMARY KEY, instrument_name VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL);
CREATE TABLE musician_instruments (musician_id INT, instrument_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (musician_id) REFERENCES musicians(musician_id), FOREIGN KEY (instrument_id) REFERENCES instruments(instrument_id));
CREATE TABLE musicians ( musician_id INT PRIMARY KEY, musician_name VARCHAR(255), birth_date DATE, instrument_id INT );
CREATE TABLE instruments ( instrument_id INT PRIMARY KEY, instrument_name VARCHAR(255) );

CREATE TABLE musician_instruments ( musician_id INT, instrument_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (musician_id) REFERENCES musicians(musician_id), FOREIGN KEY (instrument_id) REFERENCES instruments(instrument_id) );
CREATE TABLE genres ( genre_id INT PRIMARY KEY, genre_name VARCHAR(255) );

CREATE TABLE musician_groups(
    musician_id INT,
    group_id INT,
    PRIMARY KEY (musician_id, group_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (musician_id) REFERENCES musicians(musician_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (group_id) REFERENCES music_groups(group_id)
);

CREATE TABLE musician_instruments(
    musician_id INT,
    instrument_id INT,
    PRIMARY KEY (musician_id, instrument_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (musician_id) REFERENCES musicians(musician_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (instrument_id) REFERENCES instruments(instrument_id)
);
